==Arabic alphabet==

===Letter===
'''{{ARchar|ЎІ / ўАЎІ}}'''

# Althought usually considered to be the first letter of the [[Arabic]] alphabet, the small [[hamza]] ({{ARchar|[[Ў°]]}}) that sits on top of {{ARchar|[[Ў£]]}} is really the first letter of the Arabic alphabet, and the tall column is its bearer. This article only deals with the lower part, the bearer, which is called {{ARchar|[[ЎІўДўБ]]}} (вАЩ√°lif) and, without the hamza, is used to lengthen a preceding vowel, often [[a]]. It is followed by {{ARchar|[[Ў®]]}}.

